    "recap_headline": "Washington State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SAN DIEGO (March 15, 2026)\n\u2013 Washington State rallied to tie the game in the sixth inning before San Diego State answered in the later innings to post a 15-10 victory and take the series from WSU at Tony Gwynn Stadium Sunday afternoon.\nThe Cougars scored in four straight innings to erase an 8-3 deficit and tied the game at eighth after a three-run sixth inning. The Aztecs answered in a big way, scoring twice in the seventh and five more in the seventh to take the series rubber game after SDSU won the Friday opener and WSU evened the series Saturday.\nGavin Roy\n,\nMax Hartman\nand\nRyan Skjonsby\neach recorded two-hit games while Roy scored three runs, Hartman drove in two runs and\nDustin Robinson\ndrove in three runs.\nKEY MOMENTS OF THE GAME\nWSU jumped out to an early lead as\nGavin Roy\nwas hit by a pitch and\nMatt Priest\nwalked before Robinson launched a 3-2 pitch deep to centerfield for a two-run double. SDSU answered with a six-run second inning after seven hits in the inning including a grand slam to left.\nWSU began to chip away as Priest scored on a wild pitch in the third,\nNoah Thein\nsingled home a run in the fourth, Roy scored on\nDustin Robinson's\nsacrifice fly in the fifth and the Cougars tied things up in the sixth.\nDane Chavez\nscored on passed ball and Hartman pulled a two-run double to right field to tie the game at eight.\nSan Diego State took advantage of a pair of leadoff walks to plate two runs in their half of the sixth. The Aztecs pulled away with five runs in the seventh against the bullpen.\nINSIDE THE BOX SCORE\nDane Chavez\nwalked in the 6\nth\n, has reached base in 11 straight games\nGavin Roy\nsingled in the 5\nth\nto extend his hitting streak to 5 games\nTrevor Smith\nwalked in the 6\nth\nto extend his on-base streak to 15 games\nON DEC\nK\nWSU will close out its season-opening 19-game road stretch with a Tuesday afternoon matchup at Utah."
